<h1>Packet Buffer Reference</h1>

<div class="disclaimer">
  <strong>Data quality note:</strong> Information here is by <em>rumor, innuendo, and extrapolation</em>.
  Manufacturers rarely publish packet buffer information in their data sheets.
  See the <a href="/summary/">summary page</a> for context on why buffers matter,
  or read about <a href="/concepts/microburst/">microbursts</a>.
</div>

<p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#6c757d; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
  <strong>Shared memory</strong> means hardware permits buffers to be used by any port that needs them.
  In a shared memory design, it is not possible to let ALL memory go to queued packets
  (no room for new arrivals → head-of-line blocking).
  Some switches have multiple switch ICs, each managing their own memory pool — memory from one IC
  cannot be loaned to ports on another chip.
  <strong>Max TX buffer</strong> is the most a single queue/port can claim from the shared pool.
</p>

{%- set sections = switches | uniqueSections -%}

{% for section in sections %}
  {%- set rows = switches | whereSection(section) -%}

  <div class="section-header">
    {% if section == "Trident+" %}
      <a href="/concepts/trident-plus/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56840, Shared Memory, 9 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Trident II" %}
      <a href="/concepts/trident-ii/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56850/56854, Shared Memory, 12 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Mellanox" %}
      {{ section }} — Mellanox Spectrum ASIC, Shared Memory
    {% elif section == "Other Shared Memory" %}
      {{ section }} — Various ASICs
    {% elif section == "Large Queue 1RU" %}
      <a href="/concepts/deep-buffer/">{{ section }} Switches</a> — External DRAM, Very Large Buffers
    {% elif section == "Virtual Output Port (VoQ)" %}
      {{ section }} — Per-egress queues at ingress, eliminates head-of-line blocking
    {% else %}
      {{ section }}
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  <div class="buffer-table-wrap">
    <table class="buffer-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th>Port Type</th>
          <th>RX Queue</th>
          <th>TX Queue</th>
          <th>Total Buffer</th>
          <th>RX Buffer</th>
          <th>TX Buffer</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for sw in rows %}
        <tr>
          <td class="model-cell">
            {% if sw.detail_page %}
              <a class="model-link" href="/switches/{{ sw.detail_page }}/">{{ sw.model }}</a>
            {% else %}
              {{ sw.model }}
            {% endif %}
          </td>
          <td>{{ sw.port_type or "" }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.rx_queue or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.tx_queue or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.total_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.rx_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.tx_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td class="notes-cell">{{ sw.notes or "" }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

{% endfor %}

<p style="margin-top:2rem; font-size:0.82rem; color:#6c757d;">
  To add or update a switch, edit <code>_data/switches.yaml</code>.
  Each switch is one YAML block. Add a <code>detail_page</code> slug to link to a page in <code>content/switches/</code>.
</p>
